<Layout title="Real Estate Professionals · Mortgages for Architects, Builders, Brokers, Inspectors &amp; Appraisers — Multi-Source Income, Bank Statement Non-QM &amp; DSCR Florida Qualifying" description="Florida real estate professional client hub for architects + designers under Florida Statutes Chapter 481 and AIA licensure, builders + general contractors under Florida Statutes Chapter 489 with Certified General Contractor CGC license, real estate brokers under Florida Statutes Chapter 475 Part I supervisory license tier above sales associates, home inspectors under Florida Statutes Chapter 468 Part XV, and appraisers under Florida Statutes Chapter 475 Part II with USPAP Uniform Standards of Professional Appraisal Practice certification. Multi-source income synthesis under Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01 variable income with 2-year history + continuity narrative for commission and bonus and variable compensation; B3-3.2-01 self-employed borrower documentation with Form 1084 cash-flow analysis adding back depreciation + amortization + business use of home + business mileage at IRS standard rate; B3-3.4-02 partnership documentation for K-1 income from firm equity stakes; Bank Statement Non-QM as alternative qualifying path on 12-24 months business bank statement deposits for self-employed borrowers with substantial add-backs depressing AGI below qualifying capacity; P&L Statement Non-QM qualifying on CPA-prepared profit and loss statement for established business owners; Asset-Depletion Non-QM converting liquid portfolio balance to implied monthly income amortized over 360 months for HNW retirees + post-acquisition founders; DSCR Debt Service Coverage Ratio Non-QM qualifying on property rental income alone with standard ratio 1.0-1.25+ permitting investment property portfolio scaling beyond personal qualifying capacity; Conventional Conforming and Jumbo for documented borrowers; Cash-Out Refinance for business and portfolio expansion. Florida Building Code originated post-Hurricane Andrew 1992 continuing strengthening through subsequent code cycles. Hurricane reconstruction demand cycles driving builder + contractor + inspector volume across Florida hurricane events Andrew Charley Wilma Irma Michael Ian Idalia. Post-Surfside condo collapse June 2021 and Florida SB 4-D May 2022 milestone inspection + Structural Integrity Reserve Study SIRS + reserve funding requirements at 25-year and 30-year intervals for buildings 3+ stories. Florida HNW + UHNW wealth migration sustaining HNW residential design + custom home construction demand in Palm Beach + Miami-Dade + Naples + Boca Raton. NAR National Association of Realtors settlement August 17 2024 $418M implementing written buyer agency mandatory pre-showing and MLS no longer displays buyer broker compensation and openly negotiated broker compensation. Appraisal modernization continuing under FHFA guidance with hybrid appraisals + desktop appraisals + appraisal waivers expanding. Appraisal Management Companies AMCs handle substantial lender appraisal volume; appraiser employment status splits between AMC W-2 and independent fee work. Five sub-page categories with dedicated content in production: architect-designer, builder-contractor, real-estate-broker, home-inspector, appraiser. Stairway Mortgage serves Florida real estate professionals across Broward, Miami-Dade, Palm Beach, and the Treasure Coast on multi-source income synthesis." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/real-estate-professionals/">
  <div class="realprof-scope" set:html={realprofBody} />
</Layout>

